 ). A 0.7 cm hypoechogenic, well circumscribed nodule was also found in the left lobe of the thyroid. Right axillary and bilateral cervical lymph nodes were detected on US. The US results showed multiple lymph nodes in the lateral cervical region, the right was about 1.1 cm and the left was about 1 cm. Some of the dermal medulla was poorly demarcated, and dotted blood signals were seen inside the lymph modes. Thyroid function was normal.
